Conflicts: gdm3, sddm, lightdm, lxdm, xdm, slim, nodm
Description: Blue Environment Display Manager
 BEDM is a production display manager for Linux built with Rust + Tauri.
 It provides a beautiful glassmorphism login screen with:
  - PAM authentication with brute-force protection
  - Wayland and X11 session support
  - User avatar support
  - Power management (shutdown, reboot, suspend, hibernate)
  - Autologin support
  - Aurora animated background
 .
 BEDM is the default display manager for Blue Environment but
 works with any desktop session.
